results.name: a(1) = 1, a(n) = A260439(n)-th number k for which A260438(k) = A260438(n)+1; a(n) = A255551(A260438(n)+1, A260439(n)).
comment: For n > 1, a(n) = the number located immediately below n in A255551 (square array generated by Lucky sieve) in the same column where n itself is.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..25850
program: (Scheme) (define (A269369 n) (if (= 1 n) n (A255551bi (+ (A260438 n) 1) (A260439 n)))) ;; Code for A255551bi given in A255551.
